## Summary of All Changes Made

| # | Problem | Fix |
|---|---------|-----|
| 1 | `mflr` after `stwu` — wrong ABI order | Move `mflr r0` before `stwu` in prologue |
| 2 | ARM regs in volatile PPC r3-r10 — clobbered by C calls | Move ARM regs to callee-saved PPC r14-r29 |
| 3 | `PPC_CALL_TMP = r29` callee-saved used for call | Use r12 (volatile scratch) directly in `emit_call` |
| 4 | `FRAME_REGSYNC` overlaps with volatile save area | Separate `FRAME_VOLSAVE` (80) and `FRAME_REGSYNC` (112) |
| 5 | Core\* wasted a callee-saved register | Store Core\* in frame, reload with `emit_loadCore` |
| 6 | Trampoline `lwz r0,4(r1)` reads wrong location | Fix trampoline to save/restore LR at consistent frame slot |
| 7 | `emit_updateNZ` used `PPC_TMP0`/`PPC_TMP1` which aren't callee-saved | Use r3 (explicit volatile) for temporaries |
| 8 | CPSR condition mapping was wrong | Fixed `armCondToPpc` with correct CR0 bit mapping |
| 9 | `emit_loadStore` saved volatile regs to `FRAME_REGSYNC` | Save only to `FRAME_VOLSAVE`; ARM regs now callee-saved so no save needed |
| 10 | `r31` not in save/restore range | Extend save/restore loop to r14-r31 |


