The key changes in this version:

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Inline asm broken by compiler | Moved `executeBlock` to `jit_trampoline.S` — compiler cannot touch it |
| NDS "unknown instruction 00000000" | Was caused by compiler generating wrong code for the inline asm block, corrupting r1 and executing zeros |
| ISI still at ARM address | Same root cause — trampoline now correctly uses `bctrl` so block's `mflr` gets a valid PPC address |
| T-bit clearing used wrong `rlwinm` complement form | Replaced with two `rlwinm` + `or` to reliably clear bit 26 from MSB |
| `emitT_memImm` was using wrong `h` values | Fixed Thumb load/store dispatch to correctly route h=0x3..0x8 |

